			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Given issue 1712 (the Mac kernel panic with NaCl's x86-32 sandbox), we may need to use the x86-64 sandbox on Mac.  In preparation, we should make chrome_browser_tests pass for platform=x86-64 on Mac.

This will involve:
 * Using the same hack that we use for 64-bit Windows for using a 32-bit plugin with a 64-bit sel_ldr.
 * Overriding the plugin's assumption of using x86-32 on Mac somehow.
 * Fixing any other problems we encounter.
